name: George%27s_associate
content:
A Jawa bounty hunter was an associate of the alien George. The associate wore a breath mask, gloves, and brown robes. Around 9 ABY, The Jawa and other members of the Bounty Hunters' Guild confronted Din Djarin and attempted to take Grogu. However, George found Grogu adorable, and George's associate expressed interest in hugging and petting the child, a tactic which Djarin and Grogu employed multiple times.
George's associate is featured in a non-canonical section of Launchpad in Star Wars Insider 196 that was written by Jamie Cosley.
